   <abstract>This map of central Tokyo shows roads, military routes, principal streets, military installations, dependant houses, and the KU Boundary (wards). A note on the back reads "This map has been prepared especially for dependents and Allied military forces stationed in Tokyo." Fergusson marked their home in Tokyo in blue ink, No. 474, near 17th Street (the principle streets have been numbered/given Westernized names). The back includes a listing of Allied installations and dependent installations.</abstract>
   <abstract>Thomas Galloway Fergusson, a graduate of West Point, had a vast military career that included tours of Vietnam, Germany, Japan, and Korea. The American-led Allied Occupation of Japan lasted from 1945 until the signing of the Treaty of San Francisco in 1952.</abstract>
